                                  Using Gallery
                                 [GreenDot.gif]

                      Using the NRCS Photo Gallery is easy:

                             1.  Search for photos.
       * Do a quick search by selecting a State and/or a Category from the
         list boxes on the Gallery Home  page, then clicking the [BUTTON
         Input] (not implemented)__________________  button.

       * Create advanced searches on the Advanced Search  page by mixing and
         matching criteria, then clicking the [BUTTON Input] (not
         implemented)_____________________  button.

                               2.  Select a photo.
       * Search results appear as thumbnail photos with up to ten photos per
         page.

       * Click a page number or Next  below the thumbnail photos to see
         additional pages of photos.

       * Click on a thumbnail photo for an enlarged preview photo, a
         caption, and other information.

       * Click the [BUTTON Input] (not implemented)________  button to go
         the the Gallery Download page.

                             3.  Download the photo.
       * Review the available files, file types, file sizes and download
         instructions.

       * Select and click a file link to download a photo file.

                               4.  Use the photo.

       There is no charge to enhance your web site, newsletter, brochure,
      presentation, publication, or desktop with NRCS Photo Gallery photos.
                        All we ask is for a credit line:
       * Photo by (photographer's name), USDA Natural Resources Conservation
         Service

       * Photo courtesy of USDA Natural Resources Conservation Service

       * Photo by USDA NRCS

